<h1>What is Runs Of Homozygosity</h1>
<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;What is Runs Of Homozygosity (ROH)? As the name has explained, it means a consecutive runs of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Zygosity#Homozygous">homozygous</a> <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Single-nucleotide_polymorphism">Single Nucleotide Polymorphisms</a> (SNP) on a long genomic region. However, there is no agreement on exactly what length of homozygotes can be called a ROH. </p>
